Privacy Policy for Himalayan Institute App

At Himalayan Institute, we are committed to protecting the privacy of our users. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we may collect from you when you use our mobile application (the "App"), how we use that information, and the measures we take to safeguard your personal information.

1. Personal Information We Collect

When you use our App, we may collect the following types of personal information:

- Contact Information: Your name, email address, and phone number.
- Payment Information: If you purchase a paid course, we collect your payment information.
- Course Progress: We may collect information about the courses you have enrolled in and your progress within those courses.

2. How We Use Your Personal Information

We use the personal information we collect from you to:

- Provide you with access to our courses and services;
- Process payments for paid courses;
- Communicate with you about course updates and other relevant information;
- Analyze and improve our App and services;
- Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support.

We will not share your personal information with third parties, except in the following circumstances:

- When required by law;
- With our trusted service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as processing payments or sending emails;
- In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets.

3. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect the personal information we collect from you, including the use of secure servers and encryption. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

4. Your Choices

You have the right to access, modify, or delete the personal information we have collected from you. You can also choose to opt-out of receiving marketing communications from us at any time.

5. Children's Privacy

Our App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13.

6. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our App. Your continued use of our App after any such modifications will constitute your acknowledgement of the modified Privacy Policy and your agreement to be bound by its terms.

7. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at privacy@himalayaninstitute.com.
